  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Business Analyst",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong><br /></p><p>•\tRequirements Analysis & Elicitation – Prepare comprehensive Business Requirements Documents (BRDs) focused on pricing models, billing structures, and client invoicing mechanisms.</p><p>•\tDefine detailed functional specifications based on business requirements or user stories related to pricing and billing workflows.</p><p>•\tAnalyse and propose “to-be” business and operational processes for pricing and billing, perform impact assessments and estimations.</p><p>•\tCollaborate with Technology teams to ensure proposed solutions align with business needs and regulatory requirements.</p><p>•\tMonitor and manage risks/issues related to scope creep and requirement changes.</p><p>•\tTranslate business requirements into test scenarios and support User Acceptance Testing (UAT).</p><p>•\tProvide “Train-the-Trainer” sessions on pricing and billing enhancements.</p><p>•\tMaintain subject matter expertise in pricing strategies, billing systems, and corporate banking products.</p><p>•\tClarify test findings escalated by QA teams and classify them as defects or change requests.</p><p>•\tPerform impact assessments and estimations for project change requests.</p><p>•\tEnsure compliance with financial services policies, procedures, and industry practices related to billing and pricing</p><p><br /><strong>Requirements:</strong><br /></p><p>Education:</p><p>•\tBachelor’s degree in commerce, Computer Science, or related field.</p><p>•\tMBA or equivalent postgraduate qualification is preferred.</p><p>•\tProfessional certifications in Business Analysis or Financial Services are an advantage.</p><p>Essential:</p><p>•\tMinimum 10 years of experience as a Business Analyst in the Pricing & Billing domain within Corporate Banking.</p><p>•\tStrong understanding of corporate banking products including Current Accounts, Virtual Accounts, and Sub-Accounts.</p><p>•\tExperience with pricing frameworks, billing engines, invoicing cycles, and reconciliation processes.</p><p>•\tFamiliarity with KYC/CDD and account opening procedures.</p><p>•\tProven track record in analysing and implementing pricing and billing solutions with operational and technological impact assessments.</p><p>•\tUnderstanding of technology platforms and integration points (no coding required).</p><p><br /><strong>Key Domain/ Technical Skills:</strong><br /></p><p>•\tExperience in designing user journeys for pricing and billing features on digital banking channels.</p><p>•\tKnowledge of competitor offerings  in pricing and billing.</p><p>•\tExposure to API, Host-to-host, and SWIFT-based billing integrations.</p><p></p>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 10,
